reviews.text: Food and service is way below par. I’m regretted to eating here.
Food and service below average in comparison with other Crystal Jade La Mian Restaurants in Hong Kong.
Good Service

I will give the food in crystal Jade a five full stars! Pls stop here for some time if you not in a rush, feed up your tummy with traditional dimsum or noodles, xiao long bao! One minus star is because they need to improve their service, staffs never smile and speak abit rude.... but anyway, food will never let you regret!! It's on the arrival hall btw :)

reviews.text:
環境坐位尚可，但食品價格偏高，連小朋友想取杯清水也要收$9元一位(超離普)；
其它分店是免費提供清茶及水 😅

早朝に空港に着いたので朝食がてらこちらで。6:30開店。

ネットの情報を見て楽しみにしていた担々麺。思っている以上にインパクトがなくて、拍子抜け。麺が柔らかく、スープは穏やか、唐辛子の辛味は効いているが、とにかく全体がふわっとした感じ（キレがない）。小籠包は普通に美味しいです。それとコーラの3品で2000円は高いかな。でも行って損はない感じというか。

食物口味是不錯的，服務人員態度也可以。
餐廳是沒有水提供的，任何水、茶都需要付費$8。
慎入！典型態度差的服務業佼佼者！未見過咁差既知客，十問九唔應！仲要開正喺機場到境大堂，一坐低個匙已經有漬，差到極點！好似長今流放左去濟洲咁款。
態度不好，食物普通

result.name: Crystal Jade

reviews.text: If it was based solely on food it would have been 3.5 stars, considering it wasn’t bad, but if was nothing outstanding either. This is based on eating here a few times throughout the years when I land. The reason that has really left a sour note and for my family and myself to never return is the appalling service that we’ve received not once but twice. we don’t need overly warm service, even though it would be nice, but the experience is just plain rude. We have literally done nothing wrong to get such bad experience. Staff with the attitude of clearly not wanting to be there, forgetting order and then to still get it wrong when it arrives.

Do not order the famous prawn dish. Or any dish with prawns in it, refer to the photo then you know why. 

Sweet and sour fish is quite ok. Famous fried noodle doesn’t taste like it was fried, more like being boiled in the sauce. Quite expensive, two people spent over 500 HK dollars even with 10% off.

didn't have my best experience there, the staff are mediocre, not very nice, i know it gets very busy at times as it is located in the arrival hall but it DOES NOT mean that the staff can be rude and have a little attitude towards customers, you are better off going to Din Tai Fung or another crystal jade such as the one in IFC mall but i definitely DO NOT recommend going to this one, i suggest to go to terminal 2, where they have better places to eat such as Burger King or even the japanese restaurant. Never planning to go back to this branch ever again.

Anyone who has landed  in HK no need to go into town to have a taste of HK, right here you have it all.
Must try Xiao Long Bao (steamed dumplings)🤤.
Enjoy!!!!!
Simple, reasonably good food, a bit better than your average Chinese restaurant here in Vancouver where I'm from.  And this from a simple airport restaurant.  Not blown away but also not terrible.

reviews.text:
ordered a hot and sour noodles soup , tastes was bland, not worth the price at all. the old lady with a messy appearance who organized suitcase was rude and abrupt and unwelcoming. this place used to be good say like 5,6 years ago but now just overpriced bland food with bad services, not going back again

又貴又唔好食服務又差，出面安排行李個呀姐不修邊幅又冇禮貌，真係比錢買難受

If it was based solely on food it would have been 3.5 stars, considering it wasn’t bad, but if was nothing outstanding either. This is based on eating here a few times throughout the years when I land. The reason that has really left a sour note and for my family and myself to never return is the appalling service that we’ve received not once but twice. we don’t need overly warm service, even though it would be nice, but the experience is just plain rude. We have literally done nothing wrong to get such bad experience. Staff with the attitude of clearly not wanting to be there, forgetting order and then to still get it wrong when it arrives.

Do not order the famous prawn dish. Or any dish with prawns in it, refer to the photo then you know why. 

Sweet and sour fish is quite ok. Famous fried noodle doesn’t taste like it was fried, more like being boiled in the sauce. Quite expensive, two people spent over 500 HK dollars even with 10% off.

評判が良いので伺いましたが、担々麺は正直期待はずれでした。
日本のラーメン屋の担々麺とは麺が全然違います。
こちらの麺は柔らかく、にゅうめんのような食感です。
個人的にもっとかたい麺だと好みでした。
辛味はそんなに大したことないので辛さに弱い方でも平気かと思います。

小籠包は文句なしに美味しいです。
担々麺のミニサイズと小籠包のセットのようなものもお得な価格であるので普通サイズで両方注文するよりそちらのセットが良いかもしれません。

空港内なので高いと思います。入り口で人数を画面でタッチし順番待ちのチケットを取り番号が出ると呼び出され案内されます。
麺類や一通りの中華メニューです。ラーメンは日本の様なラーメンでは無く、そうめんの様な麺です。レモン水の水は言わないと出ません。
